result.name: Hassun Japanese Restaurant

reviews.text: Excellent food, very cute place. Definitely coming back!
A nice little Japanese restaurant hidden in a back alley in Tai Hang. Food is nicely prepared & fairly authentic. Price is much more reasonable than those in CWB & Central. Recommended!
Ordered omakase with the freshest of sashimi and sushi. Superb quality and presentation true to the meticulous Japanese culinary culture.
Very delicious lunch with traditional Japanese decoration. MUST TRY
Small restaurant with less than 20 seats. Simple decorated but very nice and family-feel style. Very polite and good service staff. The food is in good quality and fresh. Reasonable price.
